race.comment: SEETHRU (7) was in the money two starts back at Sandown-Hillside but was unable to repeat the effort last time when sixth at this track over 1514m. Well placed and there is no reason he cannot find winning ways. VELLASMACHINE (1) is a hulking gelding, which will help offset the 62kg and the wide gate isn't the issue it would be for some as he has no gate speed anyway. Will be thumping home. POWERBOUND (2) missed the placings two starts back then ran a better race and finished a long neck away in fourth last time out over 1620m at Donald. VIZIE (9) as continued to improve as her career progresses and she has improvement to come being only third-up.
